Frequently Asked Questions for Pacific Drilling S.A. (NYSE:PACD)
What is Pacific Drilling S.A.'s stock symbol?

Pacific Drilling S.A. trades on the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) under the ticker symbol "PACD."



When did Pacific Drilling S.A.'s stock split? How did Pacific Drilling S.A.'s stock split work?

Pacific Drilling S.A.'s stock  reverse split before market open on Wednesday, May 25th 2016. The 1-10 reverse split was announced on Tuesday, May 24th 2016. The number of shares owned by shareholders was adjusted after the closing bell on Tuesday, May 24th 2016. An investor that had 100 shares of Pacific Drilling S.A. stock prior to the reverse split would have 10 shares after the split.



How were Pacific Drilling S.A.'s earnings last quarter?

Pacific Drilling S.A. (NYSE:PACD) posted its quarterly earnings results on Thursday, February, 23rd. The company reported ($2.03) earnings per share for the quarter, topping the Thomson Reuters' consensus estimate of ($2.44) by $0.41. The business earned $177.96 million during the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $153.50 million. Pacific Drilling S.A. had a negative return on equity of 5.40% and a negative net margin of 20.08%. Pacific Drilling S.A.'s revenue was down 33.5% on a year-over-year basis. During the same quarter last year, the business posted ($0.06) earnings per share.  View Pacific Drilling S.A.'s Earnings History.



Where is Pacific Drilling S.A.'s stock going? Where will Pacific Drilling S.A.'s stock price be in 2017?

2 brokers have issued 12 month price objectives for Pacific Drilling S.A.'s stock. Their predictions range from $6.00 to $6.00. On average, they anticipate Pacific Drilling S.A.'s share price to reach $6.00 in the next twelve months. View Analyst Ratings for Pacific Drilling S.A..



Who are some of Pacific Drilling S.A.'s key competitors?

 Some companies that are related to Pacific Drilling S.A. include Profire Energy (PFIE), Pacific Coast Oil Trust (ROYT), Sundance Energy Australia (SNDE), MV Oil Trust (MVO), Vaalco Energy (EGY), Renesola (SOL), Mitcham Industries (MIND), Petroquest Energy (PQ), Sunworks (SUNW), Ion Geophysical Corporation (IO), Yingli Green Energy Holding Company Limited (YGE), SandRidge Mississippian Trust I (SDT), EXCO Resources NL (XCO), ECA Marcellus Trust I (ECT), North Atlantic Drilling (NADL), Rex Energy Corporation (REXX), SAExploration Holdings (SAEX) and Aemetis (AMTX).



Who are Pacific Drilling S.A.'s key executives?

Pacific Drilling S.A.'s management team includes the folowing people: Ron Moskovitz, Chairman of the BoardChristian J. Beckett, Chief Executive Officer, Executive DirectorPaul T. Reese, Chief Financial OfficerRobert F. MacChesney, Chief Operating OfficerCees Van Diemen, Senior Vice President of OperationsCoy Wright, Vice President Information TechnologyKinga E. Doris, Vice President, General Counsel and SecretaryJohn Boots, Vice President TreasurerMichelle Hobbs, Vice President of Human ResourcesPaul Linkin, Vice President QHSE



Who owns Pacific Drilling S.A. stock?

Pacific Drilling S.A.'s stock is owned by a number of of retail and institutional investors. Top institutional shareholders include Spark Investment Management LLC (1.02%).  View Institutional Ownership Trends for Pacific Drilling S.A..



Who sold Pacific Drilling S.A. stock? Who is selling Pacific Drilling S.A. stock?

Pacific Drilling S.A.'s stock was sold by a variety of institutional investors in the last quarter, including Spark Investment Management LLC.  View Insider Buying and Selling for Pacific Drilling S.A..



How do I buy Pacific Drilling S.A. stock? 

Shares of Pacific Drilling S.A. can be purchased through any online brokerage account. Popular online brokerages include Vanguard Brokerage Services, TD Ameritrade, E*TRADE, Scottrade, Fidelity and Charles Schwab. 



What is Pacific Drilling S.A.'s stock price today?

One share of Pacific Drilling S.A. stock can currently be purchased for approximately $1.55.


