hareholders to sell their stocks at an inflated Value. A Bear Market occurs when the overall price of offered stocks drop constantly, this allows investors to buy stocks at substantially lower prices, due to the stocks deprecated value. This particular study focuses on the periodic nature of the highest prices offered for shares of stock of the Luxembourg Energy company Pacific Drilling S.A during a four year period.Dates:Highest PricesFull transcriptMore presentations by
    
        
