Pacific Drilling - Wikipedia





















 






Pacific Drilling

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia


					Jump to:					navigation, 					search


Pacific Drilling


Type

Public company


Founded
2006


Headquarters
Luxembourg



Key people

Idan Ofer, owner


Website
pacificdrilling.com


Pacific Drilling is an offshore ultra-deepwater drilling company.[1] It is listed on the New York Stock Exchange, trading as PACD.[1][2][3]
Overview[edit]
The company was founded in 2006 by Idan Ofer, a billionaire Israeli business magnate.[4] It was listed on the Norwegian stock exchange as PDSA until 2011, when it joined the New York Stock Exchange as PACD.[4]
It is headquartered in Luxembourg, with it's corporate office located in Houston, Texas.[1] It employs a workforce of roughly 900.[1] Its Chairman is Cyril Ducau and its Chief Executive Officer is Christian J. Beckett.[1][2]
It operates drillships for exploration internationally for ultra-deepwater offshore drilling.[4] In 2011, one ship called the Pacific Bora was active in the Agbami Field near Nigeria.[4] Other ships are active in the Offshore oil and gas in the US Gulf of Mexico and in Brazil.[4]
References[edit]



^ a b c d e Pacific Drilling S.A., The Wall Street Journal
^ a b Pacific Drilling Sa (PACD:New York), Bloomberg Businessweek
^ Pacific Drilling S.A., MarketWatch
^ a b c d e Idan Ofer's Pacific Drilling files for $60m NYSE IPO, Globes, 07/11/2011






